<assessment id="u1_m2_casecc2_lbd_tutor1">
   <title>Tutor</title>
   <page><question id="q1">
      <body>
         <p>How many children were exposed to no light at all?</p>
      </body>
      <multiple_choice shuffle="false">
         <choice value="Res1">137</choice>
         <choice value="Res2">172</choice>
         <choice value="Res3">232</choice>
         <choice value="Res4">342</choice>
      </multiple_choice>
      <part>
         <response match="Res1" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. This is the number of children who are nearsighted.</feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res2" score="10">
            <feedback>Correct. The number of children who were exposed to no light at all is calculated by 155 + 17 = 172.</feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res3" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. This is the number of children who were exposed to a <em style="italic">night light</em>.</feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res4" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. This is the number of children who are not nearsighted.</feedback>
         </response>
         <hint>Look at the <link href="javascript:loadImage('../../../webcontent/flash/images/practice_caseii2q1flash1.gif')">two-way table</link>. Sum the percentage of children in the "no light" condition regardless of whether they are nearsighted.</hint>
      </part>
   </question></page>
  
</assessment>
